				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$_2$$\end{document} photoinduced interfacial hole transfer to carboxylic acid-functionalized multiwalled carbon nanotubes (MWCNT) from TiO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$_2$$\end{document}, results in hole-doped MWCNTs and reduced TiO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$_2$$\end{document}14. Nevertheless, concerning the effects of asymmetric energy dispersion on the charge transfer and photocurrent properties depending on chirality of SWCNT, there presently are no researches that consider these effects. Therefore in this research, we examine and consider these probable effects especially.

In theoretical discussion on the tight-binding model in SWCNTs, that takes into account the curvature’s effects, the formulation of the graphene sheet altered by the hopping integral between the π\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
